{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nThe `README.md` quickstart (lines ~33-53) claims to \"Run one ticket end-to-end\nacross all three surfaces\" but does not: the CLI block creates a ticket then acts on\nan unrelated hard-coded id `reel-lot-tea`; the Python block creates a **separate**\nticket; the MCP block shows only client `mcpServers` config and performs no\noperation. This misleads every audience about how rebar actually works.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Make it genuinely end-to-end** (this is now the required path, not one of two — see\nbelow): the CLI quickstart block must capture the created id from `create`\n(e.g. `--output json` piped to a shell variable) and thread that SAME ticket through\n`ready` → `claim` → `close`, so the block is a coherent, copy-pasteable, runnable\nsequence with NO hard-coded disconnected id. The Python block threads the same intent;\nthe MCP block must either perform a real operation or the prose must stop implying it\ndoes.\n\n**Why the reframe/per-surface-examples alternative is no longer admissible:** sibling\n`0435` (golden-path CI gate) EXTRACTS the README quickstart's CLI fenced block and\nexecutes those exact lines in a throwaway repo. That requires a single coherent runnable\ncommand sequence in the block. A \"disconnected per-surface examples\" reframe would leave\n0435 with no coherent block to extract/run. So this ticket MUST deliver the runnable\nend-to-end CLI block. (`0435` `depends_on` this ticket, so it lands after this fix.)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The quickstart's heading/claim matches what the code blocks actually do.\n- [ ] No hard-coded id (`reel-lot-tea`) that is disconnected from a just-created\n      ticket remains in a block that implies continuity.\n- [ ] The CLI quickstart block is a runnable single-ticket sequence (captured id\n      flows create → ready → claim → close) with no disconnected hard-coded id, and is\n      exercised verbatim by the golden-path CI smoke (sibling `0435`, which `depends_on`\n      this ticket).\n\nFiles: `README.md` (lines ~33-53)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783816809204135001,"uuid":"49a3bf51-1c45-4d9e-85df-60e5aa978291"}